Numerical results 
We remark that without loosing generality, we can choose .

Following the investigation in, we have studied the dependence of the mass
 on the cosmological constant .
It is well know that for  
global monopoles have a negative mass. Thus, the global monopole
has a repulsive effect on a test particle in its neighbourhood. The authors ofaddressed the question whether the mass can become positive for specific choices of the
cosmological constant and found that for positive cosmological
constants (Note that the sign convention in is opposite to the
one used by us, i.e. dS space has a negative cosmological constant in.)  
this is possible. As a check for a future publication on composite 
monopole defects in dS/AdS space-time, we have tried to obtain the results given inand found contradictions.

By solving the three equations numerically we constructed
solutions for positive and negative values of .
First, we checked, whether the asymptotic behaviour found in ()
is correct. We indeed confirmed numerically that the coefficients have the
given dependence on the coupling constants. We have then fixed 
and determined the mass  in dependence on .
