Since the mass curve does only alter its shape very little when choosing different ,
we conclude that in contrast to what is claimed in, the appearance of
a cosmological constant (of either sign) can not  alter the sign of the mass of the global monopole.
Rather, we find that the mass gets more negative for increasing  which can be related to the
fact that the core of the monopole increases due to increased cosmological expansion. For , we find
that the mass becomes less negative for  increasing, which is due to the decreased cosmological
expansion, but however stays negative for all values of  in AdS space.


